modules.description: This module implements an in-memory key-value store with support for time-stamped operations, partial content retrieval and updates, and directory-like hierarchies. It works with keys representing paths, string values, timestamps, and optional sizes. Use it to simulate file system operations, manage versioned in-memory data, or implement temporary storage with precise time tracking and atomic modifications.

This module implements a hierarchical key-value store with path-based keys, offering file-like operations including directory listing, atomic updates, and metadata management for timestamps and cryptographic digests. It operates on an in-memory state structure that supports structural equality checks and time initialization, making it ideal for testing hierarchical storage systems or prototyping applications requiring atomic transactions and temporal tracking. The design enables simulating complex storage behaviors with precise control over data modification and verification of state consistency.
